e network\n- No HTTPS/TLS support—suitable only for development/localhost; production deployments would need reverse proxy (nginx) or gunicorn with SSL\n- Endpoint is unauthenticated—anyone with network access can call /hello; future endpoints may need auth layer\n- Uvicorn runs directly (not gunicorn with worker pools)—acceptable for development but may need hardening for production workloads\n- Endpoint provides no request validation, error handling, or structured logging—minimal but could mask issues in production\n\n### Affected Modules\n- factory/cli.py — new `serve` command added to the root Typer app\n- factory/server.py — NEW module defining FastAPI app and /hello endpoint\n- pyproject.toml — dependencies section: added fastapi and uvicorn\n- tests/ — test_server.py and test_cli_serve.py (per memory context) test endpoint and CLI integration\n\n### Call Chain\n- User: `factory serve` → typer.run(app) dispatches to serve() function\n- serve() → validates port argument (0 ≤ port ≤ 65535) or raises Exit(1)\n- serve() → imports uvicorn and FastAPI app instance from factory.server\n- serve() → uvicorn.run(server_app, host=host, port=port) starts HTTP server in current process\n- Client: GET /hello → Starlette (FastAPI's ASGI layer) routes to hello() function\n- hello() → returns dict {'message': 'Hello, Factory!'} → FastAPI JSONResponse serializes + sends with Content-Type: application/json\n\n### Design Patterns\n- Separation of Concerns: server logic isolated in server.py, CLI handling in cli.py\n- Input Validation: port range check in CLI layer before passing to uvicorn (fail-fast principle)\n- Lazy Module Import: uvicorn and server.app imported inside serve() function to avoid import-time overhead if command not used\n- Configuration as CLI Options: host/port are parameterized with sensible defaults (127.0.0.1:8000)\n- ASGI Application: FastAPI is an ASGI framework, compatible with various deployment options (uvicorn, gunicorn, etc.)\n- Factory Pattern: serve